<br>
Take a play out of my playbook and bite their heads off a few times.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   (No, seriously, I don't do that.)<br>
<br>
Part of the problem may be your presentation.  In what you've presented, you hedge an awful lot in order to be polite.  It might serve everyone better if you were more blunt:  &quot;No, I'm sorry, I don't have the time to do that right now, but maybe some other time?&quot;<br>
<br>
Being polite doesn't mean capitulating to everyone's requests.  If you did that, you'd never get to level.<br>
<br>
I'd suggest being polite but firm.  I've turned down friends' requests when I'm dead-serious about moving tailoring up, for example, but I always let them know I'm available for future requests.<br>
<br>
I'd turn down every request to powerlevel, though.  And I might be downright rude about it, too.<br>
<br>
