 makes a good point, guildies should always be there to help each other whenever possible but there is a fine line between helping and exploitation. If you are being completely bothered by a guild member, it's your responsibility to talk to an officer and get the situation taken care of, if you can't take care of it on your own. <br>
I'm not worried about my guild when it comes to port requests when I turn 29, I enjoy helping them and they are always helping me and I am comfortable with what I should expect once I am able to group port. I feel it's part of my job within the guild itself. I don't feel like I will be overburdened with port requests 3 times an hour every hour. Should that happen however, and a guild member were to get out of hand with constant porting expectations, I am completely comfortable in talking to any of our officers and know that they would take care of the situation immediately.<br>
If you are feeling like the only reason you are even in the guild is to be their taxi, and you are not enjoying yourself at all, then you need to make some changes and have some talks and get something changed. <p>Narie<br>
