<br>
Last night at 1:45 in the morning with work the next day, she sent me a tell asking if I was about to log, which I replied that I was.  She then asked me to do several things before I log: (i) port her to surefall glade (easy enough), (ii) guiding her from surefall glade to some undislcosed location in everfrost so she could meet someone who was supposed to give here something (hmmm...this goes above and beyond your typical request) and (iii) then porting to her to some other location, which she expected to be WC.  I politely responded that I needed to log soon as I was exhausted and had work the next morning.  She then pleaded that she would give me 20pp and a telescope she insisted was worth 60pp.  I kindly replied that it wasn't about the money but that I was exhausted and really needed to sleep and suggested that I was not the only person on the server able to port her.  She then sent more tells saying it would only take a half an hour and expressing her displeasure at my actions.  I commenced to put her on my ignore list (the first so far) and logged.<br>
<br>
As they say, no good deed goes unpunished...<br>
